title: Hotbird-13F ready for launch aboard Falcon 9 from Cape Canaveral
summary: The Eutelsat Hotbird-13F geostationary communications satellite is set for launch atop a SpaceX Falcon 9 out of Cape Canaveral, Florida. The Falcon 9 booster 1069-3, which has flown the CRS-24 and Starlink 4-23 missions, is scheduled to take the Hotbird satellite to geostationary transfer orbit.
